# Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in values before running the app.

```bash
cp .env.example .env.local
```

## Client (required)

These are exposed to the browser and required for Supabase client setup.

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your-publishable-key
```

## Server (required)

```env
SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000
ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@example.com
```

`ADMIN_EMAIL` must match the email of the admin user created in Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Users.

## Server (optional — required in later phases)

```env
# Phase 3+ — admin operations and RLS bypass
SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY=your-supabase-secret-key

# Phase 5+ — contact form and newsletter email
RESEND_API_KEY=re_your_resend_api_key
EMAIL_FROM_ADDRESS=portfolio@example.com
EMAIL_REPLY_TO_ADDRESS=portfolio@example.com

# Phase 17 — Portfolio Intelligence Layer
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-key
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY=
GROQ_API_KEY=
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
NVIDIA_API_KEY=

# Encrypts CMS-stored provider keys (falls back to SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY if unset)
AI_KEYS_ENCRYPTION_SECRET=

# Rate limiting — required in production (Upstash free tier: upstash.com)
# Without these, rate limiting silently falls back to in-memory (non-functional on Vercel)
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=https://your-db.upstash.io
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=your-upstash-token
```

## Feature flags (optional)

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_SEARCH=false
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_NEWSLETTER=false
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_AI_DEMOS=false
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_PORTFOLIO_ASSISTANT=true
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_PUBLIC_NOTES=false
```

## Analytics (optional — Phase 5+)

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_ANALYTICS_ID=
```
